About

I currently have a post-doctoral position, since October 2024, at the Kaiserslautern-Landau University in the Scientific Visualization Lab, working with Christoph Garth.

Before that, I had a temporary post-doctoral position, starting December 2023, at CNRS Sorbonne Université (LIP6) within the TORI project with Julien Tierny.

My thesis (from October 2020 to December 2023), supervised by Julien Tierny, focused on the analysis of ensembles of scalar fields based on their merge trees or persistence diagrams using tools from Topological Data Analysis, with applications in feature tracking, data reduction, clustering and dimensionality reduction.

I did my master degree at Paris Descartes University (now Université Paris Cité) in the “Machine Learning for Data Science” track from 2018 to 2020.
